NVM Express (NVMe) devices are [[Article description::flash memory chips connected to a system via the PCI-E bus.]]

== Installation ==

=== Kernel ===

'''NVM Express block device''' (<var>CONFIG_BLK_DEV_NVME</var>) needs to be activated:

{{KernelBox|title=linux-4.4|1=
Device Drivers  --->
  <*> NVM Express block device      
  [*] Open-Channel SSD target support  --->
}}

Devices will show up under {{Path|/dev/nvme}}.

